articipation.Offering a discursive analysis of all British Parliamentary debates on the banning of terrorist organisations since the introduction of Britain’s current proscription regime in 2000, this book provides the first sustained treatment of this counter-terrorism power in the United Kingdom and beyond.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aNational securityzGreat BritainxHistoryy21st century. 0aProscriptionxHistoryy21st century. 0aProscriptionzGreat BritainxHistoryy21st century. 0aTerrorismxPreventionxGovernment policyzGreat Britain. 0aTerrorismxPreventionxLaw and legislationzGreat Britain. 0aTerrorist organizationszGreat BritainxHistoryy21st century. 4aPolitical Studies 2021. 4aSecurity, Conflict & Peace 2020. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Terrorism.2bisacsh  aBanning.  aDiscourse.  aListing.  aParliament.  aPolitics.  aProscription.  aRitual.  aTerrorism.  aTerrorist groups.  aTerrorist organisations.1 aJarvis, Lee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLegrand, Tim, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aLegrand, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614493540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526144935423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526144935/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles